gomodel:SYNGO_5579  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Super-resolution imaging using structured illumination microscopy (SIM) revealed that CD47 colocalized with 25% of RGC synapses in the core region of the P5 dLGN and that it colocalized with pre- and postsynaptic markers Vglut2 and Homer1, respectively (Figures 1C and S1B). Moreover, we observed CD47 in acutely isolated synaptosomes using immunostaining (Figures S6A and S6B).\n\nConsistent with presynaptic localization of CD47 to RGC inputs in the dLGN, fluorescence in situ hybridization (FISH) showed that Cd47 is expressed by cells in the ganglion cell layer (GCL) of the retina that are also positive for neuronal marker neuron-specific enolase (NSE) (Figures D and S1C), which include the presynaptic RGCs that project to the dLGN.\n\nTaken together, these results demonstrate that CD47 is localized to synapses and highly enriched in the dLGN during peak pruning, indicating that CD47 is present at the right time and place to regulate microglial engulfment during development.\". Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Immunohistochemistry\nImmunohistochemistry was performed as described in Schafer et al., 2012. Briefly, brains and eyes were harvested from mice following\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5579" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

